From 3 minutes playing, junctions are cool...<p><pre><code>    #!/usr/bin/env perl6

    if 3|4|5 == 5|6 {
        print &quot;Junction found
&quot;
    } else {
        print &quot;No junction
&quot;
    }
</code></pre>
...or using arrays this seems to be the way to do it...<p><pre><code>    #!/usr/bin/env perl6
    my @first = <3 4 5>;
    my @second = <5 6>;

    if any(@first) == any(@second) {
        print &quot;Junction found
&quot;
    } else {
        print &quot;No junction
&quot;
    }</code></pre>
